1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:13,498
Yeah, I can play the violin.

2
00:00:13,648 --> 00:00:22,146
Took lessons from time to time, but they
weren’t required.

3
00:00:22,296 --> 00:00:30,794
I mostly learned from a screen.

4
00:00:30,944 --> 00:00:39,442
I’m chill, not wired.

5
00:00:39,592 --> 00:00:48,090
I don’t need music, I don’t need rules.

6
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:56,738
I play what aches. I play what’s cool.

7
00:00:56,888 --> 00:01:05,386
Mom tunes the strings when they fall out
of line—

8
00:01:05,536 --> 00:01:14,034
But what I play? That mess is mine.

9
00:01:14,184 --> 00:01:22,682
My first violin was cardboard.

10
00:01:22,832 --> 00:01:31,330
Didn’t stop me from making sound.

11
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:39,978
I put it under my chin, then took a bow,

12
00:01:40,128 --> 00:01:48,626
Let the rhythm spin me ‘round.

13
00:01:48,776 --> 00:01:57,274
I don’t need music, I don’t need rules.

14
00:01:57,424 --> 00:02:05,922
I play what aches. I play what’s cool.

15
00:02:06,072 --> 00:02:14,570
Mom tunes the strings when they fall out
of line—

16
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:23,218
But what I play? That mess is mine.

17
00:02:23,368 --> 00:02:31,866
I practice from the couch, no concerns at
all,

18
00:02:32,016 --> 00:02:40,514
But only perform in a concert hall.

19
00:02:40,664 --> 00:02:49,162
My bow’s a wand when the lights go dim—

20
00:02:49,312 --> 00:02:57,810
I don’t play notes. I play what’s within.

21
00:02:57,960 --> 00:03:06,458
I don’t need music, I don’t need rules.

22
00:03:06,608 --> 00:03:15,106
I play what aches. I play what’s cool.

23
00:03:15,256 --> 00:03:23,754
Mom tunes the strings when they fall out
of line—

24
00:03:23,904 --> 00:03:32,402
But what I play? That mess is mine.
